- Reduced bundle size and faster initial paint

fix: prevent map choropleth flashing during zoom and search

Fixed the issue where map colors would flash from colored -> gray -> colored
when zooming or searching by addressing a race condition in data fetching.

Changes:
- Add placeholderData to React Query hooks (useCommunes, useRegions, useDepartements)
  to maintain previous data during refetches
- Remove premature updateFeatureStates call from handleMoveEnd that was causing
  updates with incomplete data
- Add 150ms debouncing to updateVisibleCodes to reduce rapid-fire updates
- Clean up unused parameters (choroplethParameter, territoryFilterCode)

fix: search not refreshing map data (gray colors after city selection)

Fixed the issue where searching for and selecting a city would leave the map
gray instead of showing colored choropleth data.

Root cause: The search component used a hardcoded 500ms setTimeout to trigger
updateVisibleCodes(), but this fired BEFORE the map finished its transition
animation. This caused it to query features at the wrong position (old location),
fetching data for the wrong area.

Solution: Remove the manual callback system entirely. The map's natural onMoveEnd
event already handles this correctly - it waits for the transition to complete
before updating visible codes and fetching the correct data.

Changes:
- Remove onSearchComplete prop and callback logic from MapSearch
- Remove handleSearchComplete and mapRefCallback plumbing from MapLayout
- Remove unused useEffect that exposed mapRef to parent in FranceMap
- Rely on map's built-in onMoveEnd event which fires after transitions complete

fix: remove debouncing from handleMoveEnd to fix search responsiveness

The 150ms debounce was causing a noticeable delay when searching for cities.
When searching for "Toulouse", the map would transition but colors would appear
150ms late, making the experience feel sluggish.

Since onMoveEnd already fires once per transition (not continuously), the
debounce was unnecessary and only added unwanted delay.

Changes:
- Remove debounce logic and useRef import from useFranceMapHandlers
- Call updateVisibleCodes immediately when onMoveEnd fires
- Colors now appear immediately after map transition completes

[BACK] MP - refacto du traitement des titulaires (#452)

Avant, dans marches.py, on partait de la liste des titulaires et on créait une ligne par marché public et titulaire.
Cela posait problème pour appliquer les modifications dans marches_enricher.py. Car la colonne modifications du dataset peut concerner des titulaires.
Maintenant, on garde la liste de titulaires à la sortie de marches.py, on applique d'abord la modifications puis on unnest les titulaires. 
Et correction du test de financial accounts
